PTPA

refers to R.A. No . 7925 or the "Public Telecommunications Policy Act of the Philippines" and its implementing rules and regulations;

(jj)

Radio frequency spectrum or Spectrum

refers to the continuous range of electromagnetic wave frequencies from 3 kilohertz up to 3,000 gigahertz;

(kk)

RAO

refers to the Reference Access Offer under Rule VI, Section 4 of this IRR;

(ll)

Satellite

refers to "communications satellites" or earth-orbiting systems capable of receiving and relaying signals to and from the ground to provide links for use in the provision of a variety of information and communications technology (ICT) services, such as telephony, radio, television, or broadband internet. For purposes of this IRR, satellites used exclusively for space/earth exploration are not included;

